  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Supremacy of God\u2019s Son"
      title: "The Supremacy of God\u2019s Son"
      number: 1
      content: '  Long ago, at many times and in many ways, God spoke to our fathers
        by the prophets, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'but in these last days he has spoken to us by his Son, whom he appointed
        the heir of all things, through whom also he created the world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He is the radiance of the glory of God and the exact imprint of his
        nature, and he upholds the universe by the word of his power. After making
        purification for sins, he sat down at the right hand of the Majesty on high, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'having become as much superior to angels as the name he has inherited
        is more excellent than theirs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For to which of the angels did God ever say,  \u201CYou are my Son,today
        I have begotten you\u201D?Or again,  \u201CI will be to him a father,and
        he shall be to me a son\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And again, when he brings the firstborn into the world, he says, 
        \u201CLet all God\u2019s angels worship him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Of the angels he says,  \u201CHe makes his angels winds,and his ministers
        a flame of fire.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But of the Son he says,  \u201CYour throne, O God, is forever and
        ever,the scepter of uprightness is the scepter of your kingdom.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "You have loved righteousness and hated wickedness;therefore God,
        your God, has anointed youwith the oil of gladness beyond your companions.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And,  \u201CYou, Lord, laid the foundation of the earth in the beginning,and
        the heavens are the work of your hands;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'they will perish, but you remain;they will all wear out like a garment,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "like a robe you will roll them up,like a garment they will be changed.[[COMMENT(0)]]But
        you are the same,and your years will have no end.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts omit '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And to which of the angels has he ever said,  \u201CSit at my right
        hand  until I make your enemies a footstool for your feet\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Are they not all ministering spirits sent out to serve for the sake
        of those who are to inherit salvation?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warning Against Neglecting Salvation'
      title: Warning Against Neglecting Salvation
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore we must pay much closer attention to what we have heard,
        lest we drift away from it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For since the message declared by angels proved to be reliable, and
        every transgression or disobedience received a just retribution, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'how shall we escape if we neglect such a great salvation? It was
        declared at first by the Lord, and it was attested to us by those who heard, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Founder of Salvation'
      title: The Founder of Salvation
      number: 4
      content: 'while God also bore witness by signs and wonders and various miracles
        and by gifts of the Holy Spirit distributed according to his will.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For it was not to angels that God subjected the world to come, of
        which we are speaking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "It has been testified somewhere,  \u201CWhat is man, that you are
        mindful of him,or the son of man, that you care for him?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You made him for a little while lower than the angels;you have crowned
        him with glory and honor,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:7 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts insert '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "putting everything in subjection under his feet.\u201DNow in putting
        everything in subjection to him, he left nothing outside his control. At
        present, we do not yet see everything in subjection to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But we see him who for a little while was made lower than the angels,
        namely Jesus, crowned with glory and honor because of the suffering of death,
        so that by the grace of God he might taste death for everyone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For it was fitting that he, for whom and by whom all things exist,
        in bringing many sons to glory, should make the founder of their salvation
        perfect through suffering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For he who sanctifies and those who are sanctified all have one source.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        That is why he is not ashamed to call them brothers,  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:11 '
        content: "Greek Or . In New Testament usage, depending on the context, the
          plural Greek word (translated \u201Cbrothers\u201D) may refer either to
          or to ; also verse 12"
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "saying,  \u201CI will tell of your name to my brothers;in the midst
        of the congregation I will sing your praise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And again,  \u201CI will put my trust in him.\u201DAnd again,  \u201CBehold,
        I and the children God has given me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Since therefore the children share in flesh and blood, he himself
        likewise partook of the same things, that through death he might destroy
        the one who has the power of death, that is, the devil, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and deliver all those who through fear of death were subject to lifelong
        slavery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For surely it is not angels that he helps, but he helps the offspring
        of Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore he had to be made like his brothers in every respect, so
        that he might become a merciful and faithful high priest in the service of
        God, to make propitiation for the sins of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: For because he himself has suffered when tempted, he is able to help
        those who are being tempted.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Greater Than Moses'
      title: Jesus Greater Than Moses
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore, holy brothers,[[COMMENT(0)]] you who share in a heavenly
        calling, consider Jesus, the apostle and high priest of our confession, '
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        content: Or ; also verse 12
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "who was faithful to him who appointed him, just as Moses also was
        faithful in all God\u2019s[[COMMENT(0)]] house. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: Greek ; also verses 5, 6
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For Jesus has been counted worthy of more glory than Moses\u2014as
        much more glory as the builder of a house has more honor than the house itself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '(For every house is built by someone, but the builder of all things
        is God.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now Moses was faithful in all God\u2019s house as a servant, to testify
        to the things that were to be spoken later, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: A Rest for the People of God'
      title: A Rest for the People of God
      number: 6
      content: "but Christ is faithful over God\u2019s house as a son. And we are
        his house, if indeed we hold fast our confidence and our boasting in our
        hope.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts insert '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore, as the Holy Spirit says,  \u201CToday, if you hear his
        voice,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'do not harden your hearts as in the rebellion,on the day of testing
        in the wilderness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'where your fathers put me to the testand saw my works for forty years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore I was provoked with that generation,and said, \u2018They
        always go astray in their heart;they have not known my ways.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  As I swore in my wrath,\u2018They shall not enter my rest.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Take care, brothers, lest there be in any of you an evil, unbelieving
        heart, leading you to fall away from the living God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But exhort one another every day, as long as it is called \u201Ctoday,\u201D
        that none of you may be hardened by the deceitfulness of sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For we have come to share in Christ, if indeed we hold our original
        confidence firm to the end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "As it is said,  \u201CToday, if you hear his voice,do not harden
        your hearts as in the rebellion.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For who were those who heard and yet rebelled? Was it not all those
        who left Egypt led by Moses? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And with whom was he provoked for forty years? Was it not with those
        who sinned, whose bodies fell in the wilderness? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And to whom did he swear that they would not enter his rest, but
        to those who were disobedient? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: So we see that they were unable to enter because of unbelief.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore, while the promise of entering his rest still stands,
        let us fear lest any of you should seem to have failed to reach it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For good news came to us just as to them, but the message they heard
        did not benefit them, because they were not united by faith with those who
        listened.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:2 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For we who have believed enter that rest, as he has said,  \u201CAs
        I swore in my wrath,\u2018They shall not enter my rest,\u2019\u201Dalthough
        his works were finished from the foundation of the world. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For he has somewhere spoken of the seventh day in this way: \u201CAnd
        God rested on the seventh day from all his works.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And again in this passage he said,  \u201CThey shall not enter my
        rest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Since therefore it remains for some to enter it, and those who formerly
        received the good news failed to enter because of disobedience, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "again he appoints a certain day, \u201CToday,\u201D saying through
        David so long afterward, in the words already quoted,  \u201CToday, if you
        hear his voice,do not harden your hearts.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For if Joshua had given them rest, God[[COMMENT(0)]] would not have
        spoken of another day later on. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:8 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So then, there remains a Sabbath rest for the people of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "for whoever has entered God\u2019s rest has also rested from his
        works as God did from his.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Let us therefore strive to enter that rest, so that no one may fall
        by the same sort of disobedience. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the word of God is living and active, sharper than any two-edged
        sword, piercing to the division of soul and of spirit, of joints and of marrow,
        and discerning the thoughts and intentions of the heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jesus the Great High Priest'
      title: Jesus the Great High Priest
      number: 13
      content: 'And no creature is hidden from his sight, but all are naked and exposed
        to the eyes of him to whom we must give account.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Since then we have a great high priest who has passed through the
        heavens, Jesus, the Son of God, let us hold fast our confession. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For we do not have a high priest who is unable to sympathize with
        our weaknesses, but one who in every respect has been tempted as we are,
        yet without sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Let us then with confidence draw near to the throne of grace, that
        we may receive mercy and find grace to help in time of need.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  For every high priest chosen from among men is appointed to act
        on behalf of men in relation to God, to offer gifts and sacrifices for sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He can deal gently with the ignorant and wayward, since he himself
        is beset with weakness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Because of this he is obligated to offer sacrifice for his own sins
        just as he does for those of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And no one takes this honor for himself, but only when called by
        God, just as Aaron was.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So also Christ did not exalt himself to be made a high priest, but
        was appointed by him who said to him,  \u201CYou are my Son,today I have
        begotten you\u201D;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "as he says also in another place,  \u201CYou are a priest forever,after
        the order of Melchizedek.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In the days of his flesh, Jesus[[COMMENT(0)]] offered up prayers
        and supplications, with loud cries and tears, to him who was able to save
        him from death, and he was heard because of his reverence. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:7 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Although he was a son, he learned obedience through what he suffered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And being made perfect, he became the source of eternal salvation
        to all who obey him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Warning Against Apostasy'
      title: Warning Against Apostasy
      number: 10
      content: 'being designated by God a high priest after the order of Melchizedek.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'About this we have much to say, and it is hard to explain, since
        you have become dull of hearing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For though by this time you ought to be teachers, you need someone
        to teach you again the basic principles of the oracles of God. You need milk,
        not solid food, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'for everyone who lives on milk is unskilled in the word of righteousness,
        since he is a child. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: But solid food is for the mature, for those who have their powers
        of discernment trained by constant practice to distinguish good from evil.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore let us leave the elementary doctrine of Christ and go
        on to maturity, not laying again a foundation of repentance from dead works
        and of faith toward God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and of instruction about washings,[[COMMENT(0)]]  the laying on of
        hands, the resurrection of the dead, and eternal judgment. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:2 '
        content: Or (that is, cleansing rites)
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And this we will do if God permits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For it is impossible, in the case of those who have once been enlightened,
        who have tasted the heavenly gift, and have shared in the Holy Spirit, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and have tasted the goodness of the word of God and the powers of
        the age to come, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and then have fallen away, to restore them again to repentance, since
        they are crucifying once again the Son of God to their own harm and holding
        him up to contempt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For land that has drunk the rain that often falls on it, and produces
        a crop useful to those for whose sake it is cultivated, receives a blessing
        from God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But if it bears thorns and thistles, it is worthless and near to
        being cursed, and its end is to be burned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Though we speak in this way, yet in your case, beloved, we feel sure
        of better things\u2014things that belong to salvation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For God is not unjust so as to overlook your work and the love that
        you have shown for his name in serving the saints, as you still do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And we desire each one of you to show the same earnestness to have
        the full assurance of hope until the end, '
      comments: []
    - name: "12: The Certainty of God\u2019s Promise"
      title: "The Certainty of God\u2019s Promise"
      number: 12
      content: 'so that you may not be sluggish, but imitators of those who through
        faith and patience inherit the promises.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For when God made a promise to Abraham, since he had no one greater
        by whom to swear, he swore by himself, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "saying, \u201CSurely I will bless you and multiply you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And thus Abraham,[[COMMENT(0)]]  having patiently waited, obtained
        the promise. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:15 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For people swear by something greater than themselves, and in all
        their disputes an oath is final for confirmation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So when God desired to show more convincingly to the heirs of the
        promise the unchangeable character of his purpose, he guaranteed it with
        an oath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'so that by two unchangeable things, in which it is impossible for
        God to lie, we who have fled for refuge might have strong encouragement to
        hold fast to the hope set before us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'We have this as a sure and steadfast anchor of the soul, a hope that
        enters into the inner place behind the curtain, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: where Jesus has gone as a forerunner on our behalf, having become
        a high priest forever after the order of Melchizedek.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Priestly Order of Melchizedek'
      title: The Priestly Order of Melchizedek
      number: 1
      content: '  For this Melchizedek, king of Salem, priest of the Most High God,
        met Abraham returning from the slaughter of the kings and blessed him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and to him Abraham apportioned a tenth part of everything. He is
        first, by translation of his name, king of righteousness, and then he is
        also king of Salem, that is, king of peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He is without father or mother or genealogy, having neither beginning
        of days nor end of life, but resembling the Son of God he continues a priest
        forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'See how great this man was to whom Abraham the patriarch gave a tenth
        of the spoils! '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And those descendants of Levi who receive the priestly office have
        a commandment in the law to take tithes from the people, that is, from their
        brothers,[[COMMENT(0)]] though these also are descended from Abraham. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But this man who does not have his descent from them received tithes
        from Abraham and blessed him who had the promises. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'It is beyond dispute that the inferior is blessed by the superior. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the one case tithes are received by mortal men, but in the other
        case, by one of whom it is testified that he lives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'One might even say that Levi himself, who receives tithes, paid tithes
        through Abraham, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Jesus Compared to Melchizedek'
      title: Jesus Compared to Melchizedek
      number: 10
      content: 'for he was still in the loins of his ancestor when Melchizedek met
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Now if perfection had been attainable through the Levitical priesthood
        (for under it the people received the law), what further need would there
        have been for another priest to arise after the order of Melchizedek, rather
        than one named after the order of Aaron? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For when there is a change in the priesthood, there is necessarily
        a change in the law as well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For the one of whom these things are spoken belonged to another tribe,
        from which no one has ever served at the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For it is evident that our Lord was descended from Judah, and in
        connection with that tribe Moses said nothing about priests.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'This becomes even more evident when another priest arises in the
        likeness of Melchizedek, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'who has become a priest, not on the basis of a legal requirement
        concerning bodily descent, but by the power of an indestructible life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For it is witnessed of him,  \u201CYou are a priest forever,after
        the order of Melchizedek.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For on the one hand, a former commandment is set aside because of
        its weakness and uselessness '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '(for the law made nothing perfect); but on the other hand, a better
        hope is introduced, through which we draw near to God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And it was not without an oath. For those who formerly became priests
        were made such without an oath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "but this one was made a priest with an oath by the one who said to
        him:  \u201CThe Lord has swornand will not change his mind,\u2018You are
        a priest forever.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'This makes Jesus the guarantor of a better covenant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The former priests were many in number, because they were prevented
        by death from continuing in office, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'but he holds his priesthood permanently, because he continues forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Consequently, he is able to save to the uttermost[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        those who draw near to God through him, since he always lives to make intercession
        for them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:25 '
        content: 'That is, completely; or '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For it was indeed fitting that we should have such a high priest,
        holy, innocent, unstained, separated from sinners, and exalted above the
        heavens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He has no need, like those high priests, to offer sacrifices daily,
        first for his own sins and then for those of the people, since he did this
        once for all when he offered up himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: For the law appoints men in their weakness as high priests, but the
        word of the oath, which came later than the law, appoints a Son who has been
        made perfect forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus, High Priest of a Better Covenant'
      title: Jesus, High Priest of a Better Covenant
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the point in what we are saying is this: we have such a high
        priest, one who is seated at the right hand of the throne of the Majesty
        in heaven, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'a minister in the holy places, in the true tent[[COMMENT(0)]] that
        the Lord set up, not man. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:2 '
        content: Or ; also verse 5
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For every high priest is appointed to offer gifts and sacrifices;
        thus it is necessary for this priest also to have something to offer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now if he were on earth, he would not be a priest at all, since there
        are priests who offer gifts according to the law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They serve a copy and shadow of the heavenly things. For when Moses
        was about to erect the tent, he was instructed by God, saying, \u201CSee
        that you make everything according to the pattern that was shown you on the
        mountain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But as it is, Christ[[COMMENT(0)]] has obtained a ministry that is
        as much more excellent than the old as the covenant he mediates is better,
        since it is enacted on better promises. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:6 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For if that first covenant had been faultless, there would have been
        no occasion to look for a second.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For he finds fault with them when he says:[[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201CBehold,
        the days are coming, declares the Lord,when I will establish a new covenant
        with the house of Israeland with the house of Judah,  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:8 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'not like the covenant that I made with their fatherson the day when
        I took them by the hand to bring them out of the land of Egypt.For they did
        not continue in my covenant,and so I showed no concern for them, declares
        the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  For this is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israelafter
        those days, declares the Lord:I will put my laws into their minds,and write
        them on their hearts,and I will be their God,and they shall be my people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And they shall not teach, each one his neighborand each one his brother,
        saying, \u2018Know the Lord,\u2019for they shall all know me,from the least
        of them to the greatest.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For I will be merciful toward their iniquities,  and I will remember
        their sins no more.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: In speaking of a new covenant, he makes the first one obsolete. And
        what is becoming obsolete and growing old is ready to vanish away.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Earthly Holy Place'
      title: The Earthly Holy Place
      number: 1
      content: '  Now even the first covenant had regulations for worship and an
        earthly place of holiness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For a tent[[COMMENT(0)]] was prepared, the first section, in which
        were the lampstand and the table and the bread of the Presence. It is called
        the Holy Place. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:2 '
        content: 'Or ; also verses 11, 21Greek '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Behind the second curtain was a second section[[COMMENT(0)]] called
        the Most Holy Place, '
      comments:
      - number: '9:3 '
        content: Greek ; also verses 6, 8
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "having the golden altar of incense and the ark of the covenant covered
        on all sides with gold, in which was a golden urn holding the manna, and
        Aaron\u2019s staff that budded, and the tablets of the covenant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Above it were the cherubim of glory overshadowing the mercy seat.
        Of these things we cannot now speak in detail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'These preparations having thus been made, the priests go regularly
        into the first section, performing their ritual duties, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'but into the second only the high priest goes, and he but once a
        year, and not without taking blood, which he offers for himself and for the
        unintentional sins of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'By this the Holy Spirit indicates that the way into the holy places
        is not yet opened as long as the first section is still standing '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '(which is symbolic for the present age).[[COMMENT(0)]] According
        to this arrangement, gifts and sacrifices are offered that cannot perfect
        the conscience of the worshiper, '
      comments:
      - number: '9:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: Redemption Through the Blood of Christ'
      title: Redemption Through the Blood of Christ
      number: 10
      content: 'but deal only with food and drink and various washings, regulations
        for the body imposed until the time of reformation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But when Christ appeared as a high priest of the good things that
        have come,[[COMMENT(0)]] then through the greater and more perfect tent (not
        made with hands, that is, not of this creation) '
      comments:
      - number: '9:11 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'he entered once for all into the holy places, not by means of the
        blood of goats and calves but by means of his own blood, thus securing an
        eternal redemption. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For if the blood of goats and bulls, and the sprinkling of defiled
        persons with the ashes of a heifer, sanctify[[COMMENT(0)]] for the purification
        of the flesh, '
      comments:
      - number: '9:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'how much more will the blood of Christ, who through the eternal Spirit
        offered himself without blemish to God, purify our[[COMMENT(0)]] conscience
        from dead works to serve the living God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:14 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore he is the mediator of a new covenant, so that those who
        are called may receive the promised eternal inheritance, since a death has
        occurred that redeems them from the transgressions committed under the first
        covenant.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:15 '
        content: The Greek word means both and ; also verses 16, 17
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For where a will is involved, the death of the one who made it must
        be established. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For a will takes effect only at death, since it is not in force as
        long as the one who made it is alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore not even the first covenant was inaugurated without blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For when every commandment of the law had been declared by Moses
        to all the people, he took the blood of calves and goats, with water and
        scarlet wool and hyssop, and sprinkled both the book itself and all the people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "saying, \u201CThis is the blood of the covenant that God commanded
        for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And in the same way he sprinkled with the blood both the tent and
        all the vessels used in worship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Indeed, under the law almost everything is purified with blood, and
        without the shedding of blood there is no forgiveness of sins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Thus it was necessary for the copies of the heavenly things to be
        purified with these rites, but the heavenly things themselves with better
        sacrifices than these. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For Christ has entered, not into holy places made with hands, which
        are copies of the true things, but into heaven itself, now to appear in the
        presence of God on our behalf. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Nor was it to offer himself repeatedly, as the high priest enters
        the holy places every year with blood not his own, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'for then he would have had to suffer repeatedly since the foundation
        of the world. But as it is, he has appeared once for all at the end of the
        ages to put away sin by the sacrifice of himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And just as it is appointed for man to die once, and after that comes
        judgment, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: so Christ, having been offered once to bear the sins of many, will
        appear a second time, not to deal with sin but to save those who are eagerly
        waiting for him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Christ\u2019s Sacrifice Once for All"
      title: "Christ\u2019s Sacrifice Once for All"
      number: 1
      content: '  For since the law has but a shadow of the good things to come instead
        of the true form of these realities, it can never, by the same sacrifices
        that are continually offered every year, make perfect those who draw near. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Otherwise, would they not have ceased to be offered, since the worshipers,
        having once been cleansed, would no longer have any consciousness of sins? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But in these sacrifices there is a reminder of sins every year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For it is impossible for the blood of bulls and goats to take away
        sins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Consequently, when Christ[[COMMENT(0)]] came into the world, he said, 
        \u201CSacrifices and offerings you have not desired,but a body have you prepared
        for me;  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:5 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'in burnt offerings and sin offeringsyou have taken no pleasure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then I said, \u2018Behold, I have come to do your will, O God,as
        it is written of me in the scroll of the book.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When he said above, \u201CYou have neither desired nor taken pleasure
        in sacrifices and offerings and burnt offerings and sin offerings\u201D (these
        are offered according to the law), "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "then he added, \u201CBehold, I have come to do your will.\u201D He
        does away with the first in order to establish the second. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And by that will we have been sanctified through the offering of
        the body of Jesus Christ once for all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And every priest stands daily at his service, offering repeatedly
        the same sacrifices, which can never take away sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But when Christ[[COMMENT(0)]] had offered for all time a single sacrifice
        for sins, he sat down at the right hand of God, '
      comments:
      - number: '10:12 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'waiting from that time until his enemies should be made a footstool
        for his feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For by a single offering he has perfected for all time those who
        are being sanctified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the Holy Spirit also bears witness to us; for after saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  \u201CThis is the covenant that I will make with themafter those
        days, declares the Lord:I will put my laws on their hearts,and write them
        on their minds,\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "then he adds,  \u201CI will remember their sins and their lawless
        deeds no more.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Full Assurance of Faith'
      title: The Full Assurance of Faith
      number: 18
      content: 'Where there is forgiveness of these, there is no longer any offering
        for sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Therefore, brothers,[[COMMENT(0)]] since we have confidence to
        enter the holy places by the blood of Jesus, '
      comments:
      - number: '10:19 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'by the new and living way that he opened for us through the curtain,
        that is, through his flesh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and since we have a great priest over the house of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'let us draw near with a true heart in full assurance of faith, with
        our hearts sprinkled clean from an evil conscience and our bodies washed
        with pure water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Let us hold fast the confession of our hope without wavering, for
        he who promised is faithful. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And let us consider how to stir up one another to love and good works, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'not neglecting to meet together, as is the habit of some, but encouraging
        one another, and all the more as you see the Day drawing near.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For if we go on sinning deliberately after receiving the knowledge
        of the truth, there no longer remains a sacrifice for sins, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'but a fearful expectation of judgment, and a fury of fire that will
        consume the adversaries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Anyone who has set aside the law of Moses dies without mercy on the
        evidence of two or three witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'How much worse punishment, do you think, will be deserved by the
        one who has trampled underfoot the Son of God, and has profaned the blood
        of the covenant by which he was sanctified, and has outraged the Spirit of
        grace? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For we know him who said, \u201CVengeance is mine; I will repay.\u201D
        And again, \u201CThe Lord will judge his people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'It is a fearful thing to fall into the hands of the living God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'But recall the former days when, after you were enlightened, you
        endured a hard struggle with sufferings, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'sometimes being publicly exposed to reproach and affliction, and
        sometimes being partners with those so treated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'For you had compassion on those in prison, and you joyfully accepted
        the plundering of your property, since you knew that you yourselves had a
        better possession and an abiding one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Therefore do not throw away your confidence, which has a great reward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For you have need of endurance, so that when you have done the will
        of God you may receive what is promised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "For,  \u201CYet a little while,and the coming one will come and will
        not delay;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "  but my righteous one shall live by faith,and if he shrinks back,my
        soul has no pleasure in him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: But we are not of those who shrink back and are destroyed, but of
        those who have faith and preserve their souls.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: By Faith'
      title: By Faith
      number: 1
      content: '  Now faith is the assurance of things hoped for, the conviction
        of things not seen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For by it the people of old received their commendation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'By faith we understand that the universe was created by the word
        of God, so that what is seen was not made out of things that are visible.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'By faith Abel offered to God a more acceptable sacrifice than Cain,
        through which he was commended as righteous, God commending him by accepting
        his gifts. And through his faith, though he died, he still speaks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'By faith Enoch was taken up so that he should not see death, and
        he was not found, because God had taken him. Now before he was taken he was
        commended as having pleased God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And without faith it is impossible to please him, for whoever would
        draw near to God must believe that he exists and that he rewards those who
        seek him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'By faith Noah, being warned by God concerning events as yet unseen,
        in reverent fear constructed an ark for the saving of his household. By this
        he condemned the world and became an heir of the righteousness that comes
        by faith.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'By faith Abraham obeyed when he was called to go out to a place that
        he was to receive as an inheritance. And he went out, not knowing where he
        was going. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'By faith he went to live in the land of promise, as in a foreign
        land, living in tents with Isaac and Jacob, heirs with him of the same promise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For he was looking forward to the city that has foundations, whose
        designer and builder is God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'By faith Sarah herself received power to conceive, even when she
        was past the age, since she considered him faithful who had promised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore from one man, and him as good as dead, were born descendants
        as many as the stars of heaven and as many as the innumerable grains of sand
        by the seashore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'These all died in faith, not having received the things promised,
        but having seen them and greeted them from afar, and having acknowledged
        that they were strangers and exiles on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For people who speak thus make it clear that they are seeking a homeland. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'If they had been thinking of that land from which they had gone out,
        they would have had opportunity to return. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But as it is, they desire a better country, that is, a heavenly one.
        Therefore God is not ashamed to be called their God, for he has prepared
        for them a city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'By faith Abraham, when he was tested, offered up Isaac, and he who
        had received the promises was in the act of offering up his only son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "of whom it was said, \u201CThrough Isaac shall your offspring be
        named.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He considered that God was able even to raise him from the dead,
        from which, figuratively speaking, he did receive him back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'By faith Isaac invoked future blessings on Jacob and Esau. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'By faith Jacob, when dying, blessed each of the sons of Joseph, bowing
        in worship over the head of his staff. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'By faith Joseph, at the end of his life, made mention of the exodus
        of the Israelites and gave directions concerning his bones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "By faith Moses, when he was born, was hidden for three months by
        his parents, because they saw that the child was beautiful, and they were
        not afraid of the king\u2019s edict. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "By faith Moses, when he was grown up, refused to be called the son
        of Pharaoh\u2019s daughter, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'choosing rather to be mistreated with the people of God than to enjoy
        the fleeting pleasures of sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He considered the reproach of Christ greater wealth than the treasures
        of Egypt, for he was looking to the reward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'By faith he left Egypt, not being afraid of the anger of the king,
        for he endured as seeing him who is invisible. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'By faith he kept the Passover and sprinkled the blood, so that the
        Destroyer of the firstborn might not touch them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'By faith the people crossed the Red Sea as on dry land, but the Egyptians,
        when they attempted to do the same, were drowned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'By faith the walls of Jericho fell down after they had been encircled
        for seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'By faith Rahab the prostitute did not perish with those who were
        disobedient, because she had given a friendly welcome to the spies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And what more shall I say? For time would fail me to tell of Gideon,
        Barak, Samson, Jephthah, of David and Samuel and the prophets\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'who through faith conquered kingdoms, enforced justice, obtained
        promises, stopped the mouths of lions, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'quenched the power of fire, escaped the edge of the sword, were made
        strong out of weakness, became mighty in war, put foreign armies to flight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Women received back their dead by resurrection. Some were tortured,
        refusing to accept release, so that they might rise again to a better life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Others suffered mocking and flogging, and even chains and imprisonment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "They were stoned, they were sawn in two,[[COMMENT(0)]]  they were
        killed with the sword. They went about in skins of sheep and goats, destitute,
        afflicted, mistreated\u2014 "
      comments:
      - number: '11:37 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts add '
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "of whom the world was not worthy\u2014wandering about in deserts
        and mountains, and in dens and caves of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And all these, though commended through their faith, did not receive
        what was promised, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: since God had provided something better for us, that apart from us
        they should not be made perfect.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus, Founder and Perfecter of Our Faith'
      title: Jesus, Founder and Perfecter of Our Faith
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore, since we are surrounded by so great a cloud of witnesses,
        let us also lay aside every weight, and sin which clings so closely, and
        let us run with endurance the race that is set before us, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Do Not Grow Weary'
      title: Do Not Grow Weary
      number: 2
      content: 'looking to Jesus, the founder and perfecter of our faith, who for
        the joy that was set before him endured the cross, despising the shame, and
        is seated at the right hand of the throne of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Consider him who endured from sinners such hostility against himself,
        so that you may not grow weary or fainthearted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In your struggle against sin you have not yet resisted to the point
        of shedding your blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And have you forgotten the exhortation that addresses you as sons? 
        \u201CMy son, do not regard lightly the discipline of the Lord,nor be weary
        when reproved by him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For the Lord disciplines the one he loves,and chastises every son
        whom he receives.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'It is for discipline that you have to endure. God is treating you
        as sons. For what son is there whom his father does not discipline? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'If you are left without discipline, in which all have participated,
        then you are illegitimate children and not sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Besides this, we have had earthly fathers who disciplined us and
        we respected them. Shall we not much more be subject to the Father of spirits
        and live? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For they disciplined us for a short time as it seemed best to them,
        but he disciplines us for our good, that we may share his holiness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For the moment all discipline seems painful rather than pleasant,
        but later it yields the peaceful fruit of righteousness to those who have
        been trained by it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore lift your drooping hands and strengthen your weak knees, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and make straight paths for your feet, so that what is lame may not
        be put out of joint but rather be healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Strive for peace with everyone, and for the holiness without which
        no one will see the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "See to it that no one fails to obtain the grace of God; that no \u201Croot
        of bitterness\u201D springs up and causes trouble, and by it many become
        defiled; "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'that no one is sexually immoral or unholy like Esau, who sold his
        birthright for a single meal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: A Kingdom That Cannot Be Shaken'
      title: A Kingdom That Cannot Be Shaken
      number: 17
      content: 'For you know that afterward, when he desired to inherit the blessing,
        he was rejected, for he found no chance to repent, though he sought it with
        tears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For you have not come to what may be touched, a blazing fire and
        darkness and gloom and a tempest '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and the sound of a trumpet and a voice whose words made the hearers
        beg that no further messages be spoken to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For they could not endure the order that was given, \u201CIf even
        a beast touches the mountain, it shall be stoned.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Indeed, so terrifying was the sight that Moses said, \u201CI tremble
        with fear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But you have come to Mount Zion and to the city of the living God,
        the heavenly Jerusalem, and to innumerable angels in festal gathering, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and to the assembly[[COMMENT(0)]] of the firstborn who are enrolled
        in heaven, and to God, the judge of all, and to the spirits of the righteous
        made perfect, '
      comments:
      - number: '12:23 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and to Jesus, the mediator of a new covenant, and to the sprinkled
        blood that speaks a better word than the blood of Abel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'See that you do not refuse him who is speaking. For if they did not
        escape when they refused him who warned them on earth, much less will we
        escape if we reject him who warns from heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "At that time his voice shook the earth, but now he has promised,
        \u201CYet once more I will shake not only the earth but also the heavens.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "This phrase, \u201CYet once more,\u201D indicates the removal of
        things that are shaken\u2014that is, things that have been made\u2014in order
        that the things that cannot be shaken may remain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Therefore let us be grateful for receiving a kingdom that cannot
        be shaken, and thus let us offer to God acceptable worship, with reverence
        and awe, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: for our God is a consuming fire.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sacrifices Pleasing to God'
      title: Sacrifices Pleasing to God
      number: 1
      content: '  Let brotherly love continue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Do not neglect to show hospitality to strangers, for thereby some
        have entertained angels unawares. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Remember those who are in prison, as though in prison with them,
        and those who are mistreated, since you also are in the body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Let marriage be held in honor among all, and let the marriage bed
        be undefiled, for God will judge the sexually immoral and adulterous. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Keep your life free from love of money, and be content with what
        you have, for he has said, \u201CI will never leave you nor forsake you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So we can confidently say,  \u201CThe Lord is my helper;  I will
        not fear;what can man do to me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Remember your leaders, those who spoke to you the word of God. Consider
        the outcome of their way of life, and imitate their faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Jesus Christ is the same yesterday and today and forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not be led away by diverse and strange teachings, for it is good
        for the heart to be strengthened by grace, not by foods, which have not benefited
        those devoted to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'We have an altar from which those who serve the tent[[COMMENT(0)]]
        have no right to eat. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For the bodies of those animals whose blood is brought into the holy
        places by the high priest as a sacrifice for sin are burned outside the camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Jesus also suffered outside the gate in order to sanctify the
        people through his own blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore let us go to him outside the camp and bear the reproach
        he endured. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For here we have no lasting city, but we seek the city that is to
        come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Through him then let us continually offer up a sacrifice of praise
        to God, that is, the fruit of lips that acknowledge his name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Do not neglect to do good and to share what you have, for such sacrifices
        are pleasing to God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Obey your leaders and submit to them, for they are keeping watch
        over your souls, as those who will have to give an account. Let them do this
        with joy and not with groaning, for that would be of no advantage to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Pray for us, for we are sure that we have a clear conscience, desiring
        to act honorably in all things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Benediction'
      title: Benediction
      number: 19
      content: 'I urge you the more earnestly to do this in order that I may be restored
        to you the sooner.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now may the God of peace who brought again from the dead our Lord
        Jesus, the great shepherd of the sheep, by the blood of the eternal covenant, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Final Greetings'
      title: Final Greetings
      number: 21
      content: 'equip you with everything good that you may do his will, working
        in us[[COMMENT(0)]] that which is pleasing in his sight, through Jesus Christ,
        to whom be glory forever and ever. Amen.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:21 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'I appeal to you, brothers,[[COMMENT(0)]] bear with my word of exhortation,
        for I have written to you briefly. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:22 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You should know that our brother Timothy has been released, with
        whom I shall see you if he comes soon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Greet all your leaders and all the saints. Those who come from Italy
        send you greetings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Grace be with all of you.
      comments: []
